Think of LLama.cpp as the engine and .gguf as the brain/weights of the model. 

# 1. Install/build llama.cpp
git clone https://github.com/ggerganov/llama.cpp
cd llama.cpp
cmake -B build
cmake --build build --config Release

# 2. Put model weights somewhere
mkdir -p models

#3 Download the model weights and put them in the models directory.
Model used: Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-Q4_K_M.gguf

#4 Run to test the functionality.
./build/bin/llama-cli \
  -m models/Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-Q4_K_M.gguf \
  -p "Explain Fourier Transform simply" \
  -n 200

-m specifies the model being used, -p specifies the prompt, and -n specifies the number of tokens to be generated.


